    </exercise>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>y=\dfrac{\frac{1}{x^2}+\frac1x+2}{x^2+\frac{2}{x^2}}</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m> \dx{y}{x} = \dfrac{(x^4+2)(4x+1)-4x^3(2x^2+x+1)}{(x^4+2)^2}\dx{x}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>y=\dfrac{x+1}{x^4+x^3+x^2+x+1}</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m> \dx{y} = \dfrac{-(3x^4+6x^2+4x^2+2x)}{(x^4+x^3+x^2+x+1)^2}\dx{x}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>y=\dfrac{x^3+3x^2-x}{x^2+3 x-1}</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m> \dx{y} = \dx{x}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
          Strange that the answer is so simple isn't it? I wonder if this is
          really an easy problem in disguise.
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>y=\dfrac{x^3-x^2-2x+2}{x-1}</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <!-- <hint> -->
