      <p>
        <m>y=\dfrac{2x+1}{7x+3}</m>
      </p>
</statement>
<answer>
        <p>
          <m> \dx{y} = \dfrac{-1}{(7x+3)^2}\dx{x}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </task>

    <task>
<statement>
      <p>
        <m>y=\dfrac{2x+5}{7x+3}</m>
      </p>
</statement>
<answer>
        <p>
          <m> \dx{y} = \dfrac{-29}{(7x+3)^2}\dx{x}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </task>
<task>
<statement>
        <p>
          What do you think the  the differential of
          <m>y=\dfrac{ax+b}{cx+d}</m> will be if <m>a, b, c,</m> and
          <m>d</m> are (arbitrary, unknown) constants? Make a conjecture.
        </p>
</statement>
</task>
<task>
<statement>
        <p>
          Check to see if your conjecture works when <m>a=-12, b=-5,
          c=2,</m> and <m>d=-17</m>.  If not, make a new conjecture and try again.
        </p>
</statement>
</task>
